Cape Town - At least four people have died after a party boat caught fire on the Hartbeespoort Dam on Saturday afternoon, the Hartbeespoort Emergency Rescue Unit reported.According to the rescue service, three people drowned and one died in the fire.&nbsp;There were about 200 people on board.Private boats helped bring people to shore.This is a developing story.MORE PICTURES from the scene. #Hartbeespoortdam Damage to the boat. Pictures:HEMS MV pic.twitter.com/Y1W95Wo1Kz24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.